subject: resource/Auja_al-Hafir
object: Auja al-Hafir, also Auja, was an ancient road junction close to water wells  in the western Negev and eastern Sinai. It was  the traditional grazing land of the 'Azazme tribe. The border crossing between Egypt and Ottoman/British Palestine, about 60 km (37 mi) south of Gaza, was situated there. Today it is the site of Nitzana and the Ktzi'ot military base in  the Southern District of Israel.
